# SEO metadata — verify before changing

The site is **not live for Google yet** (`noindex` is on in `src/layouts/Layout.astro`). Mistakes to titles, descriptions, or robots tags can hurt indexing after launch.

## Required before any edit

1. **Get explicit user approval** before changing:
   - `<title>` / page `title` passed to `<Layout>`
   - `<meta name="description">` / page `description`
   - `<meta name="robots">` / `noindex` flag in `Layout.astro`
   - `<link rel="canonical">`
   - Open Graph or Twitter meta tags
   - JSON-LD structured data in `Layout.astro` or page `<script type="application/ld+json">`

2. **Show a before/after summary** (old value → new value) in your reply so the user can confirm nothing unintended changed.

3. **Do not remove or flip `noindex`** unless the user explicitly says they are launching and want the site indexed. That change belongs in a dedicated launch step, not bundled with unrelated work.

## Do not

- Change metadata “while you’re here” on unrelated tasks.
- Copy the same title or description onto multiple pages.
- Add `noindex` to individual pages without discussing impact on launch.

